SUMMARY:Snowshoeing and Lunch - Secord Pond Intermediate
DESCRIPTION:GTA Hiking & Stuff\nWinter is nearing its end. The day after t
 his hike we Spring our clocks forward. We will snowshoe the loop around Se
 cord Pond. For those who don't have snowshoes\, you can hike behind us. Yo
 u will need your icers. This is also a good beginners snowshoe trail as th
 e terrain is relatively flat. If the conditions are favourable\, we will g
 o off trail and see the mysterious Oak Tree and explore a couple of abando
 ned buildings. Don't forget to bring your sunglasses.\n\nOur pace will be 
 determined by the trail conditions. The trail is 5-6kms in length. A good 
 distance for snowshoeing. There are several hills to climb\, but the trail
  is fairly flat. An experienced hiker should have no problem. We will have
  breaks and take in the scenery along the way.\n\n_For those who are inter
 ested\, we will have lunch at Annina's\, a local establishment in The Town
  of Goodwood._\n\n**Note**\n\n* **Snowshoes and icers are mandatory!**\n* 
 Arrive on time! Please don't let the group wait.\n* Bring water and snacks
 .\n* Dress for the conditions.\n* Free parking.\n* No dogs.\n* Having fun 
 is mandatory.\n* Know your limits! Choose the hike that matches your fitne
 ss level.\n* The hike will be posted "Canceled" if the weather doesn't coo
 perate. Fingers !\n\nTo participate in this hike\, you and guests need to 
 adhere to the rules and agree by a reply of "Yes" to the liability waiver.
 \n\n**LEGAL DISCLAIMER AND LIABILITY INFORMATION:**\nBy RSVP'ing and payin
 g the event fee (if applicable)\, you are confirming that you have read\, 
 understand\, and accept the following:\n\n1. GTA Hiking Meetup is a privat
 e group. Attending events is voluntary by you as a member. Participation i
 n any activity with us is at your own risk.\n2. By joining this event as a
  member you agree to indemnify and hold harmless its organizers\, co-organ
 izers\, assistant organizers\, event hosts\, and other members from all cl
 aims or liability of every type (including court costs and legal fees) for
  injury or death to any person or for damage to property\, loss of persona
 l property or any other wrongful act arising out of or relating to your pa
 rticipation as a member. This agreement applies to you and to other person
 s (as your guests) who may accompany you in these endeavors.\n3. You also 
 agree to hold the organizers as well as other group members harmless. By p
 articipating voluntarily in the group\, you expressly waive any and all su
 ch claims against each and every other member in the group\, including wit
 hout limitation any and all claims against the group organizer\, co-organi
 zers\, assistant organizers\, and event hosts.
